      "type": "multiple_choice",
      "question": "What does DAgger contribute in the NLG training setting?",
      "stem_format": "plain_text",
      "choices_format": "plain_text",
      "choices": [
        "It augments training with model-generated sequences so training states resemble test-time states.",
        "It computes lexical overlap between a generation and a reference.",
        "It always decodes by maximizing the model probability.",
        "It freezes the language model and changes only the tokenizer."
      ],
      "answer_index": 0,
      "explanation": "DAgger collects examples from the model's own behavior and adds them to training. This teaches the model to recover from states it is likely to create.",
