      "question": "Why can retrieval-augmented generation reduce exposure bias?",
      "stem_format": "plain_text",
      "choices_format": "plain_text",
      "choices": [
        "It starts from a retrieved prototype and edits it instead of generating every token from scratch left to right.",
        "It removes the need for any training objective.",
        "It forces the model to repeat the retrieved text exactly.",
        "It uses only BLEU as the generation policy."
      ],
      "answer_index": 0,
      "explanation": "Starting from a retrieved prototype gives the system a structured initial sequence. Editing that sequence changes the generation dynamics and reduces dependence on a fragile left-to-right prefix.",
